pkg-config is a helper tool used when compiling applications and libraries. 
It helps you insert the correct compiler options on the command line 
so an application can use gcc -o test test.cpkg-config --libs --cflags 
glib-2.0 for instance, rather than hard-coding values on where to find glib 
(or other libraries). 

It is language-agnostic, so it can be used for defining 
the location of documentation tools, for instance.

